WEBVTT

00:09.000 --> 00:11.240
<i>(Indistinct singing</i>
<i>echoing)</i>

00:13.000 --> 00:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:26.120 --> 00:28.090
(gasping)

00:35.360 --> 00:37.700
- (muffled applause)
- Woman: <i>We love you, Bessie!</i>

00:40.370 --> 00:41.900
Man:
<i>We love you, Bessie!</i>

00:48.280 --> 00:50.280
(Chatter)

00:59.660 --> 01:02.690
- Hey, Bessie...
- <i>(cheering continues)</i>

01:03.130 --> 01:06.030
- (chatter)
- Woman: <i>I love you! I love you so much!</i>

01:06.330 --> 01:08.560
- Bessie!
- <i>I love you so much!</i>

01:14.570 --> 01:16.100
<i>(Woman whispers)</i>
<i>Bessie...</i>

01:16.340 --> 01:17.800
<i>(voices echoing)</i>

01:18.170 --> 01:21.070
Man: <i>I love you, Bessie!</i>
<i>That was amazing!</i>

01:30.320 --> 01:32.420
(Door creaking)

01:37.160 --> 01:38.860
Hello?

01:42.200 --> 01:44.260
Girl:
<i>Mommy!</i>

01:44.530 --> 01:47.530
Where are you?!
(Crying)

01:48.970 --> 01:51.270
Where's my mama?

01:53.540 --> 01:55.340
<i>Mommy!</i>

01:55.680 --> 01:58.780
<i>I want her back!</i>
<i>I want my mama back!</i>

01:59.010 --> 02:00.350
<i>Where did she go?</i>

02:00.780 --> 02:04.650
- Woman: Mama ain't here to save you now.
- (Crying continues)

02:04.890 --> 02:06.720
Woman:
<i>Your mama dead.</i>

02:07.190 --> 02:11.420
- Girl: <i>Where's my mama?!</i>
- Woman: <i>It's your fault Mama dead.</i>

02:11.860 --> 02:16.160
- <i>Bessie.</i>
- Girl: <i>Where are you, Mom? Where are you?</i>

02:16.400 --> 02:19.000
Woman #2:
<i>Bessie!</i>

02:19.230 --> 02:20.930
<i>(Crying continues)</i>

02:21.300 --> 02:23.640
- <i>(music playing)</i>
- <i>(crowd cheering)</i>

02:27.880 --> 02:29.880
(overlapping voices)
You ain't part of the act.

02:30.210 --> 02:31.910
- <i>Whoo!</i>
- <i>Excuse me! Excuse me!</i>

02:32.350 --> 02:35.010
<i>Excuse me! I gotta get downstairs!</i>
<i>I gotta be changing!</i>

02:35.480 --> 02:37.620
Man: <i>Come on back here and put
on a good show for me tonight.</i>

02:38.050 --> 02:40.520
Woman: <i>I gotta change first.</i>
<i>Get on outta the way, Leroy!</i>

02:40.820 --> 02:42.190
Leroy:
<i>Tape. Let's roll tape...</i>

02:42.420 --> 02:44.220
<i>(Bessie laughing)</i>

02:44.490 --> 02:46.190
Man #2:
<i>Ooh, yeah, girl.</i>

02:46.430 --> 02:48.360
<i>(Both laughing)</i>

02:48.660 --> 02:51.770
- (man #2 moans)
- (kissing)

02:52.000 --> 02:53.430
(Bessie moans)

02:53.670 --> 02:55.570
Come here, girl.

02:55.870 --> 02:58.770
- Oh, yeah.
- (Both moaning)

03:00.280 --> 03:01.440
Ah, yeah.

03:01.710 --> 03:02.940
- Yeah.
- You like that?

03:03.180 --> 03:05.010
- Ooh.
- Yeah.

03:05.210 --> 03:06.680
Oh, that's nice.

03:08.420 --> 03:09.880
Just let me
put it in.

03:10.220 --> 03:12.390
No, I think it's just fine where it is.

03:12.720 --> 03:15.390
Oh, come on, baby.
Just a little bit.

03:15.620 --> 03:17.760
No, pap--
(cries out)

03:19.460 --> 03:21.060
Man #2:
<i>It's gonna feel real good to you.</i>

03:21.400 --> 03:23.700
- (Bessie grunts)
- (gasping, groaning)

03:25.300 --> 03:26.870
Don't mean I don't wanna
mess around a little bit.

03:27.270 --> 03:29.870
- I just didn't wanna do all of that.
- <i>(Distant applause)</i>

03:30.140 --> 03:31.200
- <i>(thuds)</i>
- Come on, now.

03:31.470 --> 03:33.470
It's just getting
good to me.

03:33.740 --> 03:35.240
- (Thuds)
- (man groans)

03:35.540 --> 03:36.710
What the hell
happened to you?

03:37.080 --> 03:39.410
- Clarence?
- I told you be here 9, 9:30.

03:39.710 --> 03:41.310
- What time is it?
- 11:00, hell!

03:41.550 --> 03:43.450
Come on,
go, go, go!

03:43.750 --> 03:45.250
Wait, wait, wait.
Give me this.

03:45.490 --> 03:46.720
<i>(Music playing)</i>

03:46.990 --> 03:48.620
Here, put this
on your head.

03:48.890 --> 03:50.720
Put that on
right now.

03:50.930 --> 03:52.230
There you go.

03:52.460 --> 03:53.990
Come on, let's go.

03:54.230 --> 03:55.530
Come on, now.

03:55.760 --> 03:57.300
That's good.
Just...

03:57.600 --> 03:59.300
<i>(crowd cheering,</i>
<i>whistling)</i>

03:59.570 --> 04:02.700
¶ Woke up this morning ¶

04:03.070 --> 04:06.710
¶ When chickens was crowing
for days... ¶

04:07.080 --> 04:08.640
<i>(overlapping voices)</i>
<i>Get her off the stage!</i>

04:08.980 --> 04:11.110
- <i>Good Lord!</i>
- <i>Just let her sing anyway.</i>

04:11.580 --> 04:15.820
- ¶ Looked on the right side of my pillow... ¶
- <i>Get off the stage!</i>

04:16.250 --> 04:20.220
- <i>(Jeering continues)</i>
- ¶ My man had gone away... ¶

04:20.690 --> 04:22.620
<i>(overlapping voices) I don't wanna hear this, man.</i>
<i>Go back inside.</i>

04:22.960 --> 04:26.190
<i>Oh, come on.</i>
<i>Just let the girl sing!</i>

04:26.430 --> 04:29.430
¶ By his pillow ¶

04:29.660 --> 04:32.470
¶ He left a note ¶

04:32.770 --> 04:36.000
¶ Reading,
"I'm sorry, Jane ¶

04:36.270 --> 04:38.370
¶ You got my goat ¶

04:39.610 --> 04:42.580
¶ No time to marry ¶

04:43.010 --> 04:48.480
- ¶ No time to settle down"... ¶
- <i>(crowd chattering)</i>

04:48.880 --> 04:51.450
- Get what everybody else gets.
- Well, we ain't everybody else.

04:51.720 --> 04:53.190
No, no, no.
You said $5, sir.

04:53.520 --> 04:55.090
A little something extra
for me and my sister.

04:55.490 --> 04:57.290
A dollar's good enough and a dollar's what you'll take.

04:57.560 --> 04:58.660
$2, sir,
for the both of us?

04:58.990 --> 05:01.130
- For a week's work?
- That's the deal.

05:01.360 --> 05:03.560
<i>(Birds chirping)</i>

05:09.840 --> 05:12.370
<i>(woman humming)</i>

05:23.650 --> 05:25.890
(humming continues)

05:38.730 --> 05:40.070
Woman:
<i>Can you see her this time?</i>

05:43.840 --> 05:46.270
- (Kissing) Hmm?
- <i>(Coins clink)</i>

05:48.210 --> 05:50.840
(kisses) You had a good week,
at least.

05:53.050 --> 05:55.010
I know washwomen
who make more.

05:55.250 --> 05:56.680
Don't be that way.

05:57.050 --> 05:59.320
Well, I'm tellin' ya,
Mama ain't satisfied.

05:59.550 --> 06:01.220
I'm gonna quit the 81.

06:01.390 --> 06:02.890
You not.

06:04.730 --> 06:06.930
Not if it means
quitting you.

06:08.300 --> 06:10.630
(Moans)

06:11.870 --> 06:15.000
- <i>(knocking on door)</i>
- (giggling)

06:15.400 --> 06:17.740
Woman #2: <i>Bessie,
you come out of there right now!</i>

06:18.110 --> 06:20.640
I told you about having
all those men in the room.

06:20.940 --> 06:22.740
Ain't no mens here,
Miss Taylor!

06:23.080 --> 06:25.350
- (Both laughing)
- Just us ladies, ma'am.

06:25.550 --> 06:28.380
<i>(Giggling)</i>

06:28.780 --> 06:29.980
Bessie: <i>Go on and take her her board.</i>
<i>She'll cool down.</i>

06:30.290 --> 06:31.420
- <i>(Coins clink)</i>
- Miss Taylor?

06:31.890 --> 06:33.820
Y'all are gonna have to take
that foolishness somewhere--

06:34.160 --> 06:34.990
- Okay.
- Miss Taylor: <i>This is not</i>

06:35.320 --> 06:37.360
<i>the only boardinghouse</i>
<i>in Atlanta.</i>

06:37.630 --> 06:40.530
<i>(Knocking)</i>
<i>Bessie!</i>

06:40.900 --> 06:42.630
Hey, look here, I'm coming
to work with you today.

06:42.900 --> 06:45.330
I gotta get me
a new act.

06:45.600 --> 06:48.070
- I like it.
- I like you.

06:48.270 --> 06:49.840
I like you, too.

06:50.140 --> 06:51.670
- (Giggling)
- <i>(knocking)</i>

06:52.010 --> 06:52.970
- <i>(music playing)</i>
- Miss Taylor: <i>Bessie!</i>

06:53.240 --> 06:55.910
Man:
<i>Good, Georgette.</i>

06:56.280 --> 06:57.580
<i>Mary Watson, if I have</i>
<i>to tell you to smile</i>

06:57.850 --> 07:00.350
one more time,
we having words.

07:00.780 --> 07:02.920
Francine, baby,
you're clomping around up there like a horse.

07:03.120 --> 07:04.750
A H-O-R-S-E.

07:05.090 --> 07:06.920
<i>Bessie, get down now.</i>
<i>Stop teasing.</i>

07:07.290 --> 07:08.820
- <i>It's not your rehearsal.</i>
- Hey, Mr. Scandrick.

07:09.160 --> 07:10.190
I've been working on
a little something.

07:10.590 --> 07:12.090
<i>Are you saying you wanna</i>
<i>be in my chorus line?</i>

07:12.430 --> 07:14.530
Yeah, come on, girls.
Let's show him.

07:14.830 --> 07:16.500
- And a...
- (piano playing)

07:18.670 --> 07:20.800
¶ Oh, I've got
what it takes ¶

07:21.140 --> 07:24.800
¶ But it breaks my heart
to give it away ¶

07:27.710 --> 07:29.680
¶ It's in demand ¶

07:29.940 --> 07:32.950
¶ They want it every day ¶

07:34.950 --> 07:36.620
¶ I've been saving it up-- ¶

07:36.950 --> 07:38.320
You just keep
right on saving it.

07:38.650 --> 07:39.990
- (Dancers laugh)
- You don't like it?

07:40.360 --> 07:42.260
It's all right, but it ain't
hitting on all the sixes.

07:42.560 --> 07:44.090
Now, if you done
messing up my rehearsal--

07:44.390 --> 07:46.090
What about the bag test,
James, hmm?

07:46.360 --> 07:48.460
Yeah, give her
the test.

07:52.830 --> 07:54.800
You must be
lighter than.

07:55.040 --> 07:57.670
(Dancers laughing)

07:57.970 --> 07:59.170
- (cheering)
- Man: <i>Whoo!</i>

07:59.540 --> 08:03.180
The top prize for tonight's raffle-- a gold tooth.

08:03.380 --> 08:04.640
That's right.

08:04.980 --> 08:05.910
Hold up them tickets.
Hold 'em up.

08:06.310 --> 08:07.750
<i>I know you got 'em.</i>
<i>I know you got 'em.</i>

08:08.050 --> 08:11.280
But first,
the Queen of Melody,

08:11.520 --> 08:13.590
the Empress of Rhythm.

08:13.990 --> 08:18.460
We're talking about
the real Mother of the Blues,

08:18.660 --> 08:22.900
Ma Rainey.

08:23.330 --> 08:24.400
- <i>(Music playing)</i>
- Ma: <i>This the real blues here.</i>

08:24.600 --> 08:25.930
<i>Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.</i>

08:35.740 --> 08:38.740
<i>(Cheering, applause)</i>

08:39.750 --> 08:43.120
¶ Ooh. ¶

08:43.350 --> 08:47.790
Audience:
¶ Ooh. ¶

08:48.090 --> 08:52.690
¶ Lord, you see me
weepin' ¶

08:52.930 --> 08:56.430
¶ And you hear me cry ¶

08:57.870 --> 09:00.130
Woman:
<i>Sing it, girl.</i>

09:01.600 --> 09:06.140
¶ Lord, you see me
weepin' ¶

09:06.410 --> 09:10.310
<i>¶ And you hear me cry ¶</i>

09:14.250 --> 09:18.680
¶ I ain't weepin'
'bout no money ¶

09:18.950 --> 09:23.960
¶ Just that man of mine ¶

09:35.070 --> 09:39.740
<i>¶ Lord, you see me</i>
<i>weepin' ¶</i>

09:40.010 --> 09:43.180
<i>¶ And you hear me cry... ¶</i>

09:45.150 --> 09:46.510
We got rehearsals
in the morning.

09:46.950 --> 09:50.180
- I could be sleeping or at least partying.
- Well, go on, then.

09:50.590 --> 09:53.020
- I just wanna meet her.
- You can meet her tomorrow.

09:53.420 --> 09:55.660
Man: <i>Mobile, Alabama,</i>
<i>we're on the road for a week,</i>

09:55.920 --> 09:57.590
<i>then Gainesville, Florida.</i>

09:58.090 --> 10:00.130
- <i>(Piano music playing)</i>
- Oh, slow, slow, slow, baby. Have mercy.

10:00.500 --> 10:03.330
Contract's only four nights,
then we can go on to--

10:03.770 --> 10:06.500
Why we backtracking to Mississippi
instead of going to 'Bama?

10:06.830 --> 10:08.170
Seem like we should
just go on from here,

10:08.540 --> 10:11.070
maybe do a longer run in Mobile,
even add Huntsville.

10:11.470 --> 10:14.070
Well, we'll be making it just in time for cotton season

10:14.440 --> 10:15.880
and catch everybody
with their pay, you know?

10:16.280 --> 10:20.080
- <i>(Distant piano music playing)</i>
- (train hissing)

10:20.280 --> 10:21.550
Oh, sh--

10:21.820 --> 10:24.380
(train whistle blows)

10:24.620 --> 10:27.150
Hey, get back here.

10:27.520 --> 10:29.220
Man: <i>Besides,
the harvest don't start in Florida</i>

10:29.520 --> 10:31.660
- <i>for another two weeks.</i>
- Mm-hmm.

10:32.030 --> 10:33.860
You've been using that goober oil like I told you?

10:34.060 --> 10:35.560
Yes, ma'am.

10:35.800 --> 10:37.360
Nice and soft.

10:37.630 --> 10:38.800
<i>Well, what about Tennessee?</i>

10:39.130 --> 10:42.130
You got Memphis,
you got Chattanoog-- oh!

10:42.500 --> 10:43.570
- <i>(Piano music stops)</i>
- How'd you get in here?

10:43.970 --> 10:46.540
- Can I join your show?
- You can see yourself out.

10:49.080 --> 10:50.540
Where you from?

10:50.850 --> 10:52.480
- Blue Goose Hollow.
- A who what?

10:52.710 --> 10:54.280
That a street name?

10:54.720 --> 10:56.380
Bessie: <i>Where I'm from,
they don't have no street names.</i>

10:56.750 --> 10:58.750
(Chuckles) That where your people from, too?

10:59.020 --> 11:00.490
They died a long time ago.

11:00.820 --> 11:02.720
Well, the loneliest thing
in the world

11:02.990 --> 11:04.260
is a motherless child.

11:04.590 --> 11:06.260
Well, I got two brothers
and my sister Viola--

11:06.530 --> 11:07.890
Well let me shave you dry.

11:08.200 --> 11:09.860
They don't amount
to much, do they?

11:10.060 --> 11:12.100
You on your own.

11:12.430 --> 11:13.670
- (Train rumbles)
- (crystals clinking)

11:14.040 --> 11:16.500
- Well, Miss Blue Goose...
- Clarence: <i>Bessie!</i>

11:16.940 --> 11:20.240
- I thank you for calling.
- Bessie! Bessie, get down from there.

11:20.740 --> 11:23.410
- Do I audition or--
- Ma: <i>I heard you in the show. I know you can sing.</i>

11:23.710 --> 11:25.850
So stay or jump, bitch.
(Chuckles)

11:26.280 --> 11:28.010
- Well, the train is--
- I don't give a damn about the train,

11:28.350 --> 11:30.950
a thunderstorm,
a shotgun or what.

11:31.250 --> 11:33.450
You just got to decide
for yourself.

11:33.760 --> 11:35.760
Hell, you got
the St. Louis blues,

11:36.090 --> 11:37.890
the Chicago blues,
the Gin House blues,

11:38.190 --> 11:40.290
the "my man
done left me" blues.

11:40.600 --> 11:42.300
They all the same song,
ain't they?

11:42.560 --> 11:44.330
With the same three chords.

11:44.870 --> 11:48.600
And you done heard 'em about a dozen
hundred times from a dozen hundred people.

11:48.940 --> 11:51.140
So what make folks
wanna hear from you?

11:52.810 --> 11:55.240
<i>So you got to put</i>
<i>something else in it.</i>

11:55.580 --> 11:59.710
The blues is not about
people knowing you.

11:59.980 --> 12:01.980
It's about
you knowing people.

12:02.250 --> 12:06.550
<i>(Train whistle blowing)</i>

12:06.750 --> 12:07.720
(patting)

12:18.900 --> 12:20.670
Who done that
to you, huh?

12:21.000 --> 12:23.970
Big old girl like you
letting folks beat on you.

12:26.240 --> 12:28.070
This look like
it might stay forever.

12:28.310 --> 12:30.810
<i>(Liquid pouring)</i>

12:31.150 --> 12:32.910
What you doing fanning yourself around here for?

12:33.250 --> 12:35.180
Shut the door good
on your way out.

12:36.450 --> 12:38.080
Where you going without my sugar, though?

12:44.990 --> 12:46.830
- Mm.
- Mm-hmm.

12:47.130 --> 12:48.760
What you grinning about,
Blue Goose?

12:49.000 --> 12:50.030
What you know about it?

12:50.260 --> 12:52.060
Same thing you know.

12:52.270 --> 12:54.500
(Chuckles)

12:54.800 --> 12:57.140
What's your name,
pretty lady?

12:57.340 --> 12:58.900
Bessie Smith.

12:59.140 --> 13:00.840
Miss Bessie Smith.

13:02.380 --> 13:03.710
<i>(Music playing)</i>

13:04.110 --> 13:06.180
- So, like we said--
- How many seats in the house?

13:06.450 --> 13:07.980
- 200.
- I counted 250.

13:08.320 --> 13:11.620
Ah, I meant 200 plus,
give or take.

13:11.890 --> 13:13.550
And you sure
eager to take.

13:13.960 --> 13:15.760
- She need to be here?
- Ma: She needs to understand

13:16.120 --> 13:17.620
why TOBA stands
for "Tough On Black Asses."

13:18.060 --> 13:21.760
Actually, it stands for Theater
Owners Booking Association, T-O-B--

13:22.060 --> 13:23.130
- What's the cover?
- <i>A nickel.</i>

13:23.400 --> 13:26.000
Hmm, newspaper ad
say a dime.

13:26.330 --> 13:28.330
- Well, we don't always--
- $12.50.

13:28.700 --> 13:31.070
- Pardon me?
- That's 10 cents times 250 seats.

13:31.370 --> 13:32.840
Our contract
is 50-50 per head.

13:33.140 --> 13:35.470
$12.50 in advance
every night.

13:35.810 --> 13:37.980
(Laughing)
We have no way of knowing

13:38.350 --> 13:39.710
how many people
are actually gonna show up.

13:39.980 --> 13:41.150
We'll refund
your no-shows.

13:41.480 --> 13:43.250
Bessie will be counting
the empty seats.

13:43.420 --> 13:45.220
$12.50.

13:48.690 --> 13:49.990
(Chuckling)

13:50.320 --> 13:51.860
Boy, aren't you getting
a hell of a deal?

13:53.190 --> 13:54.690
Now let's talk about
the bar.

14:03.540 --> 14:05.400
What you standing
way back here for?

14:05.610 --> 14:07.010
Keep on going.

14:11.180 --> 14:13.050
I ain't said stop.

14:17.050 --> 14:18.280
A little bit more.

14:21.220 --> 14:23.090
- Ma.
- <i>That's about right.</i>

14:24.090 --> 14:25.060
Now how that feel?

14:25.290 --> 14:26.930
Like I'm about to fall.

14:27.260 --> 14:29.200
That's how it should feel every night.

14:29.460 --> 14:31.200
If you're not
risking nothing,

14:31.430 --> 14:32.930
neither will they.

14:33.270 --> 14:36.300
Now where's that heifer
that stole your man?

14:36.600 --> 14:39.870
- Ain't nobody here.
- Pick somebody.

14:40.140 --> 14:42.040
Right there.
How about her?

14:42.310 --> 14:44.540
Three rows back
on the left.

14:48.050 --> 14:50.450
- Mm-mmm.
- Yeah.

14:51.950 --> 14:53.050
Yeah, that look
like her.

14:53.390 --> 14:54.790
And what you gotta
say to that bitch?

14:54.990 --> 14:56.420
<i>And right there.</i>

14:56.820 --> 15:00.160
Oh, there's that pinched-back
man that stole all your money.

15:02.960 --> 15:04.230
Yeah, that's him.

15:04.600 --> 15:07.470
Tell them about theyselves.
Go on, baby.

15:12.440 --> 15:14.640
- Bess? We're rehitching.
- Okay.

15:14.840 --> 15:16.240
<i>(Men shouting)</i>

15:38.670 --> 15:40.470
That mighty caboose
right there.

15:42.340 --> 15:44.970
<i>(Chatter)</i>

15:54.520 --> 15:56.650
- Man: <i>That was Bertha-- I mean, Miss Bessie Smith.</i>
- <i>(Piano playing)</i>

15:57.120 --> 16:01.650
- (scattered applause)
- Man: <i>Aw, come on now, be nice, be nice.</i>

16:01.990 --> 16:04.490
<i>We got your headliner</i>
<i>coming up.</i>

16:05.990 --> 16:07.530
Gin.

16:10.500 --> 16:11.900
I got that, Clive.

16:12.130 --> 16:13.900
<i>(Coins clink)</i>

16:14.140 --> 16:15.870
Gin'll make you crazy.

16:16.200 --> 16:18.840
Why don't you let me buy you a whiskey instead?

16:20.880 --> 16:22.810
That "stand and shout" shit
might work back home,

16:23.240 --> 16:27.050
but you got to bring some hoop-de-doo
to get these silly folk attention.

16:27.350 --> 16:28.950
Don't nobody care
what you think.

16:29.250 --> 16:30.920
You don't know nothin'
from nothin'.

16:31.250 --> 16:34.420
Oh, I ain't trying to fuss with you, gorgeous.

16:34.760 --> 16:35.990
Just 'cause you got
a little sport in your strut

16:36.260 --> 16:37.420
don't make you
no authority.

16:37.760 --> 16:39.990
I was just giving you
my opinion, that's all.

16:41.230 --> 16:42.700
I'm gonna see you
later tonight.

16:43.000 --> 16:46.500
- Not hardly.
- Yeah, you will.

16:50.100 --> 16:51.900
- <i>(Cheering, applause)</i>
- Hey.

16:52.110 --> 16:54.140
Say, you seen Ma?

16:54.510 --> 16:57.010
(Chuckles) You were just talking to her.

16:57.240 --> 16:59.350
<i>(Music playing)</i>

17:05.619 --> 17:08.220
¶ I went out last night ¶

17:08.520 --> 17:11.119
¶ With a crowd
of my friends ¶

17:11.530 --> 17:15.829
¶ Must have been women,
'cause I don't like no men ¶

17:16.130 --> 17:20.130
¶ Wear my clothes
just like a fan ¶

17:20.470 --> 17:24.540
¶ Talk to the gals
just like any old man ¶

17:24.770 --> 17:27.210
¶ They say I do it ¶

17:27.480 --> 17:29.580
¶ Ain't nobody caught me ¶

17:29.880 --> 17:34.410
¶ Sure got to
prove it on me... ¶

17:34.750 --> 17:36.850
Oh, wait a minute now,
wait a minute now.

17:37.280 --> 17:40.050
I see some of your eyes rolling,
trying to find my Johnson.

17:40.290 --> 17:41.790
That ain't ladylike.

17:42.120 --> 17:45.290
Trust me, mama,
I got everything you need.

17:45.460 --> 17:46.660
Ha!

17:49.100 --> 17:51.830
<i>(Audience shouting,</i>
<i>laughing)</i>

17:52.100 --> 17:54.170
¶ 'Cause they say I do it ¶

17:54.440 --> 17:56.240
¶ Ain't nobody caught me ¶

17:56.500 --> 18:01.040
¶ Sure got to
prove it on me ¶

18:01.340 --> 18:04.310
¶ Sure got
to prove it on me. ¶

18:04.510 --> 18:06.810
<i>(Cheering)</i>

18:12.150 --> 18:13.750
I almost got her
to go to bed with me.

18:14.160 --> 18:15.550
- (Laughter)
- Bessie: <i>You ain't almost nothing.</i>

18:15.760 --> 18:17.660
What?

18:17.990 --> 18:19.990
Oh, ain't no "almost"
right here, baby.

18:20.290 --> 18:22.090
- (Both moaning)
- All: Ooh-hoo!

18:22.330 --> 18:23.730
Ma get more tail
than me.

18:23.960 --> 18:25.700
<i>(All chuckling)</i>

18:25.970 --> 18:27.870
What you looking
'round for?

18:28.100 --> 18:29.370
Who gonna see ya?

18:29.640 --> 18:31.170
<i>And so what if they do?</i>

18:31.470 --> 18:33.910
They got to prove it
on you, baby.

18:34.110 --> 18:35.410
(Laughter)

18:35.710 --> 18:38.540
They got to prove it
on you, baby.

18:41.020 --> 18:42.510
(Knocking)

18:45.820 --> 18:46.990
- (laughter)
- Shit, like they doing something bad.

18:47.220 --> 18:49.690
What they doing, baby?

18:49.890 --> 18:51.690
Go on with that.

18:51.990 --> 18:53.430
Let the cards
do the talking.

18:53.730 --> 18:55.430
Let the cards do
the motherfucking talking.

18:55.730 --> 18:57.560
What the fuck
was she talking about?

18:59.170 --> 19:01.030
Take that bullshit on back
where you got it from.

19:01.400 --> 19:03.800
I told you,
you ain't ready for the big leagues.

19:04.040 --> 19:06.240
<i>(Laughter, chatter)</i>

19:13.410 --> 19:17.180
Oh!
(Laughing)

19:17.420 --> 19:19.750
<i>(music playing)</i>

19:25.090 --> 19:26.930
<i>(crowd cheering)</i>

19:31.530 --> 19:35.400
<i>¶ Lord, you see me</i>
<i>weepin' ¶</i>

19:35.670 --> 19:39.610
<i>¶ And you hear me cry ¶</i>

19:44.910 --> 19:49.150
¶ Lord, you see me
weepin' ¶

19:49.420 --> 19:53.250
¶ And you hear me cry ¶

19:57.760 --> 20:02.390
¶ I ain't weepin'
'bout no money ¶

20:02.630 --> 20:06.730
¶ Just that man
of mine ¶

20:11.370 --> 20:16.040
¶ Lord, this mean
old engineer ¶

20:16.280 --> 20:20.550
¶ Cruel as he could be ¶

20:25.150 --> 20:29.420
¶ This mean old engineer ¶

20:29.660 --> 20:33.590
¶ Cruel as he could be ¶

20:35.760 --> 20:37.800
(crowd cheering)

20:38.100 --> 20:41.970
Both:
¶ Took my man away ¶

20:42.300 --> 20:47.170
¶ And blowed the smoke
back at me ¶

20:47.410 --> 20:51.240
¶ Back at me ¶

20:51.480 --> 20:56.150
¶ I'm going down South ¶

20:56.420 --> 21:00.590
¶ Won't be back till fall ¶

21:00.820 --> 21:04.260
¶ Back till fall ¶

21:04.530 --> 21:07.890
¶ I'm going down South... ¶

21:08.100 --> 21:09.290
Crowd: Yeah!

21:09.600 --> 21:12.930
¶ Won't be back
till fall ¶

21:17.040 --> 21:22.310
¶ If I don't find
my easy rider ¶

21:22.610 --> 21:26.280
¶ Ain't comin' back
at all ¶

21:26.610 --> 21:28.850
- Woman: <i>Bessie!</i>
- <i>(Crowd cheering)</i>

21:30.350 --> 21:35.120
¶ Yeah, if I don't find
my easy rider... ¶

21:35.520 --> 21:40.630
- Come on, Bessie!
- ¶ Ain't comin' back at all ¶

21:40.860 --> 21:44.200
¶ Back at all. ¶

21:44.400 --> 21:45.700
(Cheering)

21:52.470 --> 21:53.410
Yeah, Bessie!

21:55.010 --> 21:56.280
Clarence:
<i>Yeah!</i>

21:56.580 --> 21:58.240
(Stammering)
You can't control that.

21:58.550 --> 22:00.150
- Her goddamn ego--
- Whoo-hoo hoo!

22:00.480 --> 22:02.920
I ain't never
seen 'em like that!

22:03.150 --> 22:05.320
We sung that song.

22:05.590 --> 22:08.020
Yeah, I earned
this tonight.

22:08.260 --> 22:09.520
<i>(Laughing)</i>
<i>Oh, yeah.</i>

22:09.890 --> 22:11.320
<i>Come on, Ma,</i>
<i>you ain't gonna drink no co--</i>

22:11.660 --> 22:13.360
I know you ain't drinking
no corn with me.

22:19.700 --> 22:21.870
Remember what I told you
about the blues?

22:23.870 --> 22:26.970
About you knowing the people
and not the other way around?

22:27.170 --> 22:29.210
Yeah.

22:29.580 --> 22:32.340
I knowed everybody in there
and they knowed me.

22:32.580 --> 22:36.010
You sure love yourself.

22:36.450 --> 22:39.920
<i>I see that gin done finally made you blow your top, huh?</i>

22:43.060 --> 22:44.360
I did good.

22:44.690 --> 22:48.030
It's not a matter
of you doing good.

22:48.400 --> 22:49.860
You're just busted 'cause they was yelling for me

22:50.130 --> 22:51.930
more than they was
yelling for you.

22:52.230 --> 22:54.900
You better turn
your damper down.

22:55.300 --> 22:58.040
- I ain't scared of you.
- I ain't never asked you to be.

22:58.310 --> 22:59.740
All I asked you for
was respect.

23:00.070 --> 23:02.670
Respect for yourself,
respect for these songs.

23:03.110 --> 23:04.980
I ain't see you respect all this
extra money I'm bringing in here.

23:05.310 --> 23:07.910
Oh, let me get you told,
little gal,

23:08.280 --> 23:10.320
'cause I can see you ain't
learnt your lesson yet.

23:10.580 --> 23:12.480
It's my name
on this train,

23:12.750 --> 23:13.850
it's my name
on those flyers,

23:14.220 --> 23:17.060
and it is in my name
that everybody in this company

23:17.290 --> 23:18.590
takes to that stage.

23:18.930 --> 23:20.490
Now, until you can
get yourself together,

23:20.930 --> 23:24.200
you're going back to deucing,
'cause you ain't ready to headline.

23:24.470 --> 23:25.660
- Deucing?
- <i>Deucing.</i>

23:25.830 --> 23:27.470
No.

23:27.800 --> 23:30.000
I ain't playing second
to nobody anymore.

23:32.410 --> 23:34.170
Best we shake hands
and go.

23:35.980 --> 23:37.810
<i>Well, Miss Blue Goose...</i>

23:39.080 --> 23:41.310
take off
my goddamn shoes.

24:02.100 --> 24:03.870
What's wrong?
What happened?

24:04.270 --> 24:05.470
- Bessie: We're starting our own show.
- Our own show?

24:05.870 --> 24:06.970
- We're just getting started.
- I'm finished with starting.

24:07.310 --> 24:08.770
Wait, Bessie,
I'm gonna go talk to Ma.

24:09.040 --> 24:10.540
Hey, don't leave.
I'm coming!

24:12.380 --> 24:13.980
<i>(Chatter)</i>

24:14.450 --> 24:16.880
- Man: The 3:00 with service...
- Clarence: They're coming, all right?

24:23.620 --> 24:24.690
All right,
don't give me that face now.

24:24.990 --> 24:27.990
Just relax.
They're coming.

24:35.570 --> 24:36.700
(Man shouting)

24:36.970 --> 24:39.440
- Ha ha!
- Hey, man!

24:39.740 --> 24:41.870
- How you feeling?
- You all right?

24:44.080 --> 24:46.450
Bobby, you know
I'd catch you.

24:46.750 --> 24:48.310
- (Laughing)
- Good to see you.

24:48.550 --> 24:50.880
So good to see you.

24:51.190 --> 24:53.090
Man:
<i>It's corn bread time.</i>

24:53.490 --> 24:55.490
The money gonna come in soon.
Thank y'all for heaven.

24:55.890 --> 24:57.460
Clarence: <i>Sure.
This ain't nothing like it used to be.</i>

24:57.760 --> 24:59.060
You want some more
of these greens?

24:59.390 --> 25:00.660
Clarence: <i>You know,</i>
<i>I ain't nervous yet.</i>

25:00.990 --> 25:02.430
You have to take
the show on the road.

25:02.760 --> 25:04.730
Hip, too.
Get a piano on the ground floor.

25:05.030 --> 25:06.970
We're gonna take
good care of you.

25:07.270 --> 25:09.330
'Cause what we're doing
here, man, is

25:09.670 --> 25:11.200
we're bringing a little South to the North.

25:11.610 --> 25:14.010
A little taste of home for all these homesick Yankees.

25:14.370 --> 25:15.870
You know what I'm saying?
They ain't ready for it.

25:16.210 --> 25:17.180
They ain't ready for it,
but I'm telling you,

25:17.510 --> 25:19.540
Bessie's doing
big things, man, and...

25:19.850 --> 25:21.380
<i>you on bass,</i>
<i>you on horn.</i>

25:21.780 --> 25:26.350
Next, we have Doreen Dupree
from Hattiesburg, Mississippi.

25:29.120 --> 25:30.920
Is that a real name
or a made-up one?

25:31.260 --> 25:33.090
- Hattiesburg is a real--
- Not Hattiesburg.

25:33.430 --> 25:34.890
I know where in the hell Hattiesburg is.

25:35.200 --> 25:37.100
I'm talking about
"Doreen Dupree."

25:37.460 --> 25:39.500
That sound like some made-up,
store-bought shit to me.

25:39.900 --> 25:41.830
Don't that sound like some old vaudeville mess to you?

25:42.270 --> 25:44.440
Who mama and daddy gonna name
'em something go together like that?

25:44.770 --> 25:46.570
You pick that out of a magazine or something?

25:46.870 --> 25:48.240
It's on
my birth certificate.

25:48.610 --> 25:52.480
They have birth certificates
in Hattiesburg, Mississippi?

25:52.780 --> 25:54.010
And take that damn gum
out your mouth.

25:54.410 --> 25:57.150
Don't nobody wanna see you
up there chewing like a cow.

25:57.580 --> 26:01.090
- Where do I put it?
- Hold it in your damn hand, Hattiesburg.

26:04.090 --> 26:06.930
(Whispers)
Five, six, seven, eight.

26:07.230 --> 26:09.290
Wait, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

26:09.500 --> 26:11.530
What is that?

26:11.770 --> 26:13.270
Um, I'm dancing, ma'am.

26:13.630 --> 26:15.070
- <i>I wanna--</i>
- You better sing something first.

26:15.440 --> 26:17.340
<i>(Stammering)</i>
<i>I don't know how to sing.</i>

26:17.600 --> 26:19.910
You don't know
how to sing?

26:20.270 --> 26:22.510
You wanna be in my show,
you have to be able to sing,

26:22.810 --> 26:25.110
dance, and tell
a damn joke or two.

26:27.750 --> 26:29.550
(Clears throat)

26:29.850 --> 26:31.150
¶ Well, I woke up
this morning-- ¶

26:31.490 --> 26:34.290
That's enough.
Clarence, give her the bag test.

26:37.020 --> 26:38.460
What you grinning for?

26:38.660 --> 26:40.030
You failed.

26:40.430 --> 26:43.200
You must be darker than the bag to be in my show.

26:43.530 --> 26:45.360
Now get going with
your high-heeled ass.

26:45.800 --> 26:49.070
- Next!
- Clarence: <i>Etta Johnson, Bell Buckle, Tennessee.</i>

26:49.300 --> 26:50.940
Bell Buckle?
Lord!

26:51.170 --> 26:53.240
No yellow bitches.

26:53.470 --> 26:55.170
- (Yelps)
- Next!

26:55.540 --> 26:58.980
- Next!
- What if I didn't pass your bag test?

26:59.380 --> 27:03.150
- I never give you no test.
- Oh, you test me... daily.

27:06.320 --> 27:08.290
No, you--
you tell me.

27:08.490 --> 27:10.560
Come on, Lucy.

27:10.720 --> 27:13.330
No.

27:13.530 --> 27:16.260
I wanna know.

27:16.530 --> 27:19.330
Would you still
love me?

27:19.570 --> 27:21.170
You'd still be you.

27:21.470 --> 27:23.170
And how would you
know that?

27:23.400 --> 27:25.570
You know how I feel.

27:29.180 --> 27:30.540
Then I need you
to say it.

27:30.840 --> 27:32.610
- You know.
- No, I don't know.

27:32.810 --> 27:34.250
You know.

27:35.580 --> 27:37.050
Then say it.

27:39.190 --> 27:40.820
It wouldn't matter.

27:41.090 --> 27:42.150
It wouldn't matter,
what?

27:42.490 --> 27:44.520
It wouldn't matter
about your color.

27:47.590 --> 27:49.260
And?

27:49.430 --> 27:51.230
And?

27:53.530 --> 27:54.930
You know what?

28:01.280 --> 28:03.170
I cares for you.

28:04.880 --> 28:07.080
(Chuckles)

28:07.280 --> 28:09.180
You cares for me?

28:10.880 --> 28:13.050
You cares for me.
Is that all?

28:13.290 --> 28:13.990
No, that ain't all.

28:14.350 --> 28:17.360
What-- why you
acting up today?

28:17.620 --> 28:20.230
I need you
to tell me something.

28:20.630 --> 28:24.360
- I'm gonna show you something instead.
- (Laughing)

28:27.200 --> 28:29.100
Clarence: <i>You can make this bigger.</i>
<i>You know what I mean?</i>

28:29.440 --> 28:30.970
<i>It's got to say,</i>
<i>"This is Bessie Smith,"</i>

28:31.440 --> 28:34.540
<i>so make this bigger and this a little bit smaller like that.</i>

28:37.280 --> 28:39.410
Now, that's what-- that's what I'm talkin' about,
right there.

28:39.610 --> 28:41.710
(Chatter)

28:46.050 --> 28:48.120
Clarence:
Come on. All right.

28:50.590 --> 28:51.990
Clarence:
<i>Open your eyes!</i>

28:53.960 --> 28:57.030
- Hey now!
- Clarence: <i>That's right.</i>

28:57.330 --> 28:59.430
<i>Bessie Smith</i>
<i>and Her Down Home Trio.</i>

29:01.840 --> 29:04.340
- Ho-ho, now!
- That's right.

29:04.740 --> 29:06.810
- ¶ I was with you, baby... ¶
- <i>(crowd cheering)</i>

29:07.110 --> 29:11.610
¶ When you didn't
have a dime ¶

29:16.250 --> 29:18.920
¶ I was with you,
baby ¶

29:19.190 --> 29:23.320
¶ When you didn't
have a dime ¶

29:27.460 --> 29:31.230
<i>¶ Now, since you got</i>
<i>plenty of money ¶</i>

29:31.600 --> 29:35.770
¶ You have throwed
your good gal down... ¶

29:36.000 --> 29:38.200
<i>(crowd cheering)</i>

29:41.140 --> 29:43.240
<i>(overlapping voices) This is A.R.</i>
<i>Knight from the "Chicago Defender,"</i>

29:43.610 --> 29:44.640
<i>and I'm here to tell you</i>
<i>that Bessie Smith</i>

29:45.010 --> 29:47.050
<i>is the locomotive</i>
<i>that shot out of Tennessee.</i>

29:47.450 --> 29:49.750
<i>This is W. Alexander</i>
<i>from the "Boston Guardian."</i>

29:50.050 --> 29:51.550
<i>Talk about</i>
<i>"Chattanooga Choo-Choo,"</i>

29:51.950 --> 29:54.490
<i>Bessie Smith is the biggest thing since Ma Rainey.</i>

29:54.960 --> 29:57.560
<i>This is J. Anderson reporting for</i>
<i>the "New York Amsterdam News."</i>

29:58.020 --> 30:00.020
<i>If you haven't got your tickets, folks,</i>
<i>you're not gonna get 'em,</i>

30:00.330 --> 30:01.630
<i>'cause it's already</i>
<i>sold out.</i>

30:01.860 --> 30:03.330
<i>(Knocking on door)</i>

30:11.840 --> 30:13.810
<i>(knocking continues)</i>

30:14.010 --> 30:15.510
Who is it?

30:15.880 --> 30:17.380
Man: <i>I'm here to audition for Miss Bessie Smith.</i>

30:17.810 --> 30:19.810
I didn't ask you what you want,
I asked you who you are.

30:20.150 --> 30:22.150
Man: <i>Open the door and see me,
big man.</i>

30:33.730 --> 30:35.930
My name is Jack Gee, ma'am,
and I'm 32 years old

30:36.360 --> 30:38.760
from Titustown, Virginia,
and I schooled till the 10th grade.

30:39.100 --> 30:40.730
I'm nobody's husband
and I'm nobody's daddy.

30:41.200 --> 30:46.300
I make $13.75 a week working as a
security guard at the five and dime.

30:46.670 --> 30:49.240
Another $2.80 on the weekend at the Top Hat.

30:49.580 --> 30:50.680
<i>I got my own</i>
<i>two-bedroom apartment</i>

30:51.040 --> 30:53.950
<i>and I drive a brand-new</i>
<i>1921 Davis Touring.</i>

30:54.350 --> 30:56.150
Now, I don't believe in church,
but I do believe in God,

30:56.520 --> 30:58.150
and I know it to be
the God's honest truth

30:58.450 --> 30:59.750
that you're
the most beautiful woman

31:00.090 --> 31:05.590
ever sing the blues,
or any woman, period.

31:06.060 --> 31:08.960
And I'm very pleased to make your
acquaintance this fine afternoon.

31:09.230 --> 31:10.730
- Can you sing?
- Oh, yes.

31:10.960 --> 31:12.530
- Can you dance?
- Oh, yes.

31:12.800 --> 31:14.230
Auditions for the show
are over.

31:14.530 --> 31:16.630
I ain't auditioning
for no show.

31:16.940 --> 31:18.640
I'm auditioning
to be your man.

31:18.940 --> 31:20.610
(Scoffs)
You look a little small.

31:20.940 --> 31:23.140
- Baby, I'm built for speed.
- Really, now?

31:23.440 --> 31:25.580
Well, maybe you only
auditions women.

31:26.980 --> 31:30.880
I auditions
whosoever I please.

31:31.220 --> 31:32.680
I can give it
as hard as I can take it,

31:32.950 --> 31:35.920
and I don't mind
going to jail.

31:46.000 --> 31:52.500
- Jack: <i>Mm-mm-mm.</i>
- Woman: <i>¶ Whoa, gone away, baby ¶</i>

31:52.810 --> 31:55.910
<i>¶ Won't be back</i>
<i>till fall ¶</i>

31:56.140 --> 31:58.180
<i>¶ Lord, Lord, Lord ¶</i>

31:58.510 --> 32:02.280
<i>¶ Gone away, baby,</i>
<i>won't be back... ¶</i>

32:02.620 --> 32:04.480
Bottle of gin for the lady
and a glass for me.

32:08.520 --> 32:12.520
<i>¶ If I find me</i>
<i>a good man ¶</i>

32:12.830 --> 32:16.160
<i>¶ I won't be</i>
<i>back at all... ¶</i>

32:16.500 --> 32:19.200
- (men chuckling)
- Oh, she fine. Man.

32:21.100 --> 32:22.500
Man:
<i>Watch this.</i>

32:24.700 --> 32:27.840
- The lady don't smoke.
- The hell she don't.

32:28.040 --> 32:29.310
(Chuckles)

32:31.980 --> 32:33.580
So that's your man
or what?

32:33.850 --> 32:35.650
No, he's still auditioning.

32:35.850 --> 32:37.820
(Men laughing)

32:38.120 --> 32:40.390
Can I have
this dance, baby?

32:40.720 --> 32:42.450
Touch her hand, Charlie,
and draw back a nub.

32:42.690 --> 32:44.460
And what if I touch his?

32:44.790 --> 32:46.160
- (Knife clicks)
- (Bessie gasps)

32:46.460 --> 32:47.390
- <i>(women scream)</i>
- Ah!

32:53.300 --> 32:54.430
Man:
<i>Hey! Yeah, come here!</i>

32:54.800 --> 32:56.570
- Jack: Come on, girl.
- (Bessie laughing)

32:56.970 --> 32:58.540
- Let's go get 'em, okay?
- Get that motherfucker!

32:58.870 --> 33:00.970
- <i>(Tires screeching)</i>
- (Bessie laughing)

33:01.340 --> 33:03.210
- Chump!
- Bessie: <i>You were so brave, papa!</i>

33:03.510 --> 33:05.180
See how crazy I am
about you, girl!

33:07.980 --> 33:10.250
- Your audition ain't over yet.
- (Honking)

33:10.480 --> 33:11.350
(women screaming)

33:11.650 --> 33:13.280
Keep your eyes
on the road.

33:13.650 --> 33:15.290
- <i>(Belt buckle clinking)</i>
- (chuckles)

33:15.590 --> 33:18.190
<i>¶ A good man</i>
<i>is hard to find ¶</i>

33:18.530 --> 33:21.530
<i>¶ You always get</i>
<i>the other kind ¶</i>

33:21.900 --> 33:25.060
<i>¶ Just when you think</i>
<i>that he's your pal... ¶</i>

33:25.330 --> 33:27.200
Say, we still
$15 short.

33:27.600 --> 33:30.570
- 10 is what everybody gets.
- But we had a contract, sir.

33:31.000 --> 33:32.740
Contract?
You must be one of them old country niggers.

33:33.010 --> 33:34.840
(Chuckling)
Contra--

33:35.110 --> 33:36.980
I'll cut you
every way but loose.

33:37.380 --> 33:40.180
<i>¶ Hug him in the morning,</i>
<i>kiss him every night ¶</i>

33:40.580 --> 33:41.880
<i>¶ Give him plenty of lovin',</i>
<i>you know what I mean ¶</i>

33:42.350 --> 33:45.320
<i>¶ And treat him right,</i>
<i>'cause a good man nowadays... ¶</i>

33:45.750 --> 33:47.550
Bessie: And remember when we
did that show at Don's place?

33:48.020 --> 33:49.520
- Clarence: Ah, you don't remember that.
- Bessie: Oh, lookit.

33:49.790 --> 33:51.620
Lookit, J.G.
That's our corner.

33:52.060 --> 33:54.590
- That's our corner.
- Clarence: A penny a song. (Laughs)

33:55.060 --> 33:56.960
- Woman: I love you, Bessie!
- You see that gin joint right there?

33:57.300 --> 33:59.030
That's where I made
my first whole dollar.

33:59.530 --> 34:02.500
- Spent it, too.
- <i>¶ Hug him in the morning, kiss him every night ¶</i>

34:02.900 --> 34:05.470
<i>¶ Give him plenty of lovin',</i>
<i>treat him right ¶</i>

34:05.870 --> 34:10.040
<i>¶ 'Cause a good man nowadays</i>
<i>is hard to find ¶</i>

34:10.380 --> 34:12.280
<i>¶ Ah, yes,</i>
<i>hard to find... ¶</i>

34:12.580 --> 34:14.280
- How y'all doing?
- Oh, my God.

34:14.580 --> 34:18.620
¶ A good man
is hard to find ¶

34:18.920 --> 34:22.120
¶ You always get
another kind ¶

34:22.420 --> 34:25.489
<i>¶ So if your man</i>
<i>is nice ¶</i>

34:25.889 --> 34:29.130
- <i>¶ Take my advice...</i>
- Come over here right now.

34:30.600 --> 34:32.400
- You know all them words?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

34:32.670 --> 34:33.969
You know
what you're singing?

34:36.440 --> 34:39.500
Hold out your hand
right now.

34:44.340 --> 34:46.409
Keep singing.

34:46.750 --> 34:49.650
Make sure all
you're doing is singing.

34:52.850 --> 34:55.920
- Boy: <i>Come on, let's go.</i>
- (Children giggling)

34:59.460 --> 35:01.590
<i>(young Bessie crying)</i>

35:01.830 --> 35:04.500
Mommy. Where's my mama?

35:04.830 --> 35:09.030
<i>- (Child giggling)</i>
<i>- (crying continues)</i>

35:14.710 --> 35:16.410
Man: Welcome home.
Come on inside.

35:16.710 --> 35:18.980
- Man #2: Hey, hey!
- (Men laughing)

35:19.310 --> 35:21.650
Hey y'all. How you doing?
How you doing?

35:42.740 --> 35:47.640
Well, I guess you think
you're something.

35:50.180 --> 35:51.910
How are you?

35:52.080 --> 35:53.680
You care?

35:54.050 --> 35:58.880
I think I'm gonna go show
Jack and Lucille around.

36:12.270 --> 36:13.500
That's your man?

36:16.370 --> 36:18.540
You got something
to eat?

36:18.840 --> 36:22.110
- Drink?
- Oh, city gal, huh?

36:22.510 --> 36:25.940
Can't stand to be in regular
folks' houses no more.

36:33.550 --> 36:34.890
You still keeps
the food locked up.

36:35.090 --> 36:37.290
That's right.

36:37.560 --> 36:40.220
Y'all was like
little rats.

36:40.590 --> 36:42.530
How else was I supposed to
keep the food in the house

36:42.860 --> 36:45.900
- and feed six people?
- Come here.

36:46.230 --> 36:48.700
Go get a case of Coca-Cola
and a lot of ice.

36:49.070 --> 36:52.040
As many potato chips
and peanuts as you can get.

36:52.240 --> 36:55.910
Oh, golly. Mm.

36:56.210 --> 36:59.210
A whole case
of Coca-Cola.

36:59.550 --> 37:03.580
After 10 years,
ain't you a saint?

37:10.260 --> 37:11.390
Don't drink it all up.

37:11.620 --> 37:13.190
You're one to talk.

37:13.590 --> 37:14.960
Well, you're the one still
keeps the food locked up.

37:15.300 --> 37:16.890
Don't look like you're
missing no meals.

37:17.230 --> 37:19.400
Well, I sure didn't
get 'em here, did I?

37:25.170 --> 37:28.170
I got some tickets
for the show tonight.

37:28.470 --> 37:29.540
You want to bring
the family...

37:29.810 --> 37:30.910
I got someplace
else to be.

37:46.190 --> 37:48.660
You been by
Mama's grave yet?

38:04.980 --> 38:07.810
Lucy: No street signs,
no lights, no nothing.

38:08.180 --> 38:09.810
Bessie: Told ya, Mama,
this is Blue Goose Hollow.

38:10.180 --> 38:12.020
I know this town better than J.G.'s ding-a-ling.

38:12.220 --> 38:14.190
(All laughing)

38:14.450 --> 38:16.120
Yeah, this is my town!

38:16.390 --> 38:18.820
Woman:
<i>Hey, Bessie! Hey.</i>

38:19.060 --> 38:22.030
<i>(Crowd cheering)</i>

38:34.240 --> 38:37.210
Woman: Oh, you remember.
I know you remember...

38:42.720 --> 38:46.120
Woman: Easy, papa.
Leave room for the Holy Ghost, now.

38:46.420 --> 38:48.450
Man: Good times with you two.

38:48.820 --> 38:50.690
Woman #2: Girl,
you gotta get your man.

38:50.990 --> 38:53.490
- Hey.
- Leave them gals be.

38:53.730 --> 38:55.860
- Yeah.
- Get off of me.

38:56.230 --> 38:58.160
- What do you think this is?
- I said leave 'em be!

38:58.400 --> 39:00.830
Shut up, fat bitch.

39:01.200 --> 39:02.930
- What'd that fucker say to me?
- I said--

39:03.200 --> 39:04.040
- (thuds)
- (man yells)

39:08.440 --> 39:10.410
- (whistling)
- (cheering)

39:12.010 --> 39:14.450
- (applause)
- Don't nobody try her.

39:14.710 --> 39:17.520
She's in her gin, y'all.

39:33.900 --> 39:36.570
...your little dancer

39:36.870 --> 39:40.000
decided to come along
for the ride.

39:40.240 --> 39:43.340
Y'all know how to ball!

39:43.640 --> 39:46.310
And we're gonna
ball again tomorrow.

39:48.780 --> 39:51.320
- (Woman screaming)
- Man: Hey, get back here!

39:54.650 --> 39:56.450
Woman:
<i>Clarence, help us.</i>

39:59.090 --> 40:02.130
- Where's a doctor?
- Clarence: <i>Get somebody!</i>

40:04.500 --> 40:07.060
- Get somebody! Hurry up.
- Baby, look at me. Look at me.

40:07.270 --> 40:08.670
<i>Oh, shit.</i>

40:08.840 --> 40:10.370
<i>Help!</i>

40:10.570 --> 40:13.100
Help!

40:13.270 --> 40:14.070
Baby...

40:14.270 --> 40:15.770
<i>(shushing)</i>

40:16.110 --> 40:18.880
- Lucy: Bessie!
- Clarence: Hurry up!

40:19.080 --> 40:20.410
Bessie!

40:20.680 --> 40:24.250
- <i>Bessie! Bessie!</i>
- Mommy!

40:24.480 --> 40:25.920
- <i>Bessie!</i>
- Mommy!

40:26.150 --> 40:29.150
- Bessie!
- No!

40:29.360 --> 40:30.690
(Screaming)

40:35.160 --> 40:36.960
Where's my mommy?

40:39.170 --> 40:40.930
Where's Mama?

40:41.170 --> 40:43.930
(Screaming, crying)

40:46.970 --> 40:50.410
Jack: <i>It's okay.</i>
<i>It's okay, baby.</i>

40:50.810 --> 40:52.880
- Baby, it's okay.
- Get off of me! Get off of me!

40:53.210 --> 40:55.050
- Get off of me!
- She's okay. She's okay.

40:57.380 --> 40:58.920
- Why did you--
- I'm right here, baby.

40:59.320 --> 41:01.450
- You let her get me.
- I ain't going nowhere, I love you.

41:01.850 --> 41:03.590
Jack <i>You gotta let that heal.</i>
<i>You gotta let that heal.</i>

41:03.990 --> 41:05.990
- Bess, you gotta let that heal.
- We got a show to do.

41:06.360 --> 41:06.990
Clarence: No, no,
ain't no show. Ain't no show.

41:07.190 --> 41:09.760
Lucy: Bess!

41:09.960 --> 41:11.630
Jack: <i>Bess!</i>

41:11.800 --> 41:12.860
Bess!

41:13.200 --> 41:15.770
- Lucy: <i>Nurse!</i>
- Bess, what are you doing?

41:15.970 --> 41:17.330
(Chattering)

41:21.370 --> 41:23.010
<i>(crowd cheering)</i>

41:26.680 --> 41:28.250
How much y'all pay
to get in here?

41:28.510 --> 41:31.920
- Crowd: 25 cents.
- 25 cent?

41:32.290 --> 41:35.790
Hmm, I wouldn't pay 25 cent
to go nowhere.

41:41.530 --> 41:44.230
Well, I guess I better
sing something, huh?

41:44.530 --> 41:47.930
'Cause y'all spent
all that money.

41:48.170 --> 41:51.140
<i>(Music playing)</i>

42:19.200 --> 42:20.660
Man:
<i>"Dear Miss Smith,</i>

42:21.000 --> 42:22.900
<i>my name is</i>
<i>Harry Herbert Pace,</i>

42:23.270 --> 42:25.540
<i>president of the newly formed</i>
<i>Black Swan Records</i>

42:25.840 --> 42:28.070
<i>based in Harlem,</i>
<i>New York City.</i>

42:28.410 --> 42:29.740
<i>I'm a great admirer</i>
<i>of your work,</i>

42:30.010 --> 42:31.410
<i>having seen you perform</i>

42:31.740 --> 42:35.050
<i>at the Royal Theater</i>
<i>in Philadelphia.</i>

42:35.410 --> 42:38.180
<i>News of your great talent</i>
<i>continues to precede you</i>

42:38.550 --> 42:40.650
<i>and we would like to invite you</i>
<i>to an audition</i>

42:41.050 --> 42:43.250
<i>at our offices in Times Square,</i>
<i>New York City,</i>

42:43.720 --> 42:47.060
to be our first recording artist
signed to the Black Swan label!

42:47.360 --> 42:49.030
- Hoo!
- Well, this is it.

42:49.430 --> 42:51.300
I always wanted to live in New York City,
you know.

42:51.700 --> 42:52.630
You're gonna be the biggest
thing since Mamie Smith.

42:53.030 --> 42:53.960
You know how many records
she sold last year?

42:54.300 --> 42:56.470
- Bessie: A million.
- A colored outfit?

42:56.770 --> 42:58.370
Ain't nobody heard of
no Black Swan.

42:58.740 --> 43:00.970
<i>What you need is a national label.</i>
<i>Big-time.</i>

43:01.370 --> 43:03.040
W.E.B. Du Bois' company
wants to record you, sis.

43:03.280 --> 43:04.980
This is the big time!

43:05.380 --> 43:07.510
- So? I read his book.
- I doubt you read his book.

43:07.750 --> 43:09.350
I read the damn book.

43:09.780 --> 43:12.150
- What's that got to do with music?
- This is the big ticket.

43:12.550 --> 43:14.590
Bessie, this is what they're
calling Pan-Africanism.

43:14.890 --> 43:16.090
Well, what about
Pan-Americanism?

43:16.460 --> 43:18.660
Can she sell more tickets?
That's what I wanna know.

43:18.960 --> 43:20.890
"The only genuine
colored records.

43:21.230 --> 43:23.390
The others are only
passing for colored."

43:23.730 --> 43:25.460
- That's their motto.
- I like that.

43:25.670 --> 43:26.930
I like it, too.

43:27.270 --> 43:30.470
"Yours in negritude,
Harry Herbert Pace."

43:30.740 --> 43:32.170
The fuck is negritude?

43:32.470 --> 43:35.070
That means they're real,
real black.

43:35.310 --> 43:36.740
My kind of people.

43:41.010 --> 43:42.980
Talk about passing.

43:43.320 --> 43:45.380
Y'all is fried, dyed,
and laid to the side.

43:45.750 --> 43:47.750
Well, and we are very
excited to be here.

43:48.250 --> 43:50.520
- <i>Very excited.</i>
- We were surprised you could schedule the audition

43:50.860 --> 43:52.190
so quickly given your
busy tour schedule.

43:52.530 --> 43:55.760
We canceled the rest of
our tour to be here.

43:56.200 --> 43:59.000
- Well, that's, uh--
- Well, y'all wanna hear me sing, right?

43:59.270 --> 44:01.570
Yes. Yes, yes,
of course.

44:01.870 --> 44:03.700
Is there anything else
that you need?

44:04.000 --> 44:05.470
I need a little something
for this tea.

44:05.710 --> 44:08.210
Honey, sugar, milk?

44:08.510 --> 44:11.110
Splash of Old Tom
will be just fine.

44:11.340 --> 44:13.710
- "Old Tom"?
- Gin?

44:13.950 --> 44:15.750
I'm sorry, I-- I--

44:16.150 --> 44:19.620
I don't know that we have any
or where we could find any.

44:19.850 --> 44:21.990
You see, it's, ah...

44:22.360 --> 44:24.050
- I mean, it's illegal.
- Never mind. It's okay.

44:24.290 --> 44:26.060
No, it ain't okay.

44:27.630 --> 44:31.100
You want her at her best,
then give her what she needs.

44:31.330 --> 44:33.030
Oh, it's okay, papa.

44:35.700 --> 44:38.500
(Vocalizing)

44:38.700 --> 44:40.100
¶ Oh... ¶

44:40.370 --> 44:43.510
(clears throat)
Hold up.

44:43.740 --> 44:44.610
Something ain't right.

44:44.810 --> 44:46.580
<i>¶ Oh-- ¶</i>

44:46.810 --> 44:49.510
Ahem--
(snorts)

44:49.720 --> 44:51.720
(retches)

44:55.350 --> 44:58.020
¶ I got a man I love ¶

44:59.930 --> 45:02.590
<i>¶ Why he had</i>
<i>to leave me? ¶</i>

45:02.860 --> 45:06.600
<i>¶ I got a man I love ¶</i>

45:06.870 --> 45:08.200
¶ Smart as he can be... ¶

45:09.900 --> 45:11.540
<i>(clears throat)</i>

45:13.970 --> 45:16.070
Dear Miss Smith,

45:16.380 --> 45:19.840
while we appreciate your
downhome sound,

45:20.150 --> 45:21.810
we do not feel
that it is a fit

45:22.050 --> 45:23.710
for Black Swan Records.

45:24.020 --> 45:25.320
We have chosen
to record instead

45:25.650 --> 45:28.620
<i>a young lady who</i>
<i>we unanimously agree</i>

45:28.890 --> 45:31.890
<i>has a more</i>
<i>compatible sound</i>

45:32.190 --> 45:33.720
<i>and is a bright,</i>
<i>shining example</i>

45:34.130 --> 45:36.390
<i>of the Harlem Renaissance</i>
<i>and an uplift to the race.</i>

45:36.660 --> 45:38.500
<i>We hope you can appreciate</i>

45:38.800 --> 45:40.160
<i>the difficulty</i>
<i>of our decision</i>

45:40.500 --> 45:42.030
<i>and the choices</i>
<i>that must be made</i>

45:42.300 --> 45:44.270
<i>in the name of progress.</i>

45:44.570 --> 45:46.070
<i>We remain admirers</i>
<i>of your work</i>

45:46.410 --> 45:47.840
<i>and hope that you will</i>
<i>keep us in mind</i>

45:48.140 --> 45:49.210
<i>for your</i>
<i>future recordings.</i>

45:49.580 --> 45:51.310
Jack: <i>You let her go in there and make a damn fool</i>

45:51.710 --> 45:53.510
- <i>out of herself.</i>
- Pour me another glass of this corn.

45:53.880 --> 45:55.210
- Ain't nobody crying.
- It was a good meeting, man.

45:55.510 --> 45:57.150
<i>Hey, baby, look here.</i>
<i>Never again.</i>

45:57.520 --> 45:58.980
Damn fools don't know nothing
about no talent.

45:59.320 --> 46:00.720
I'm gonna get you
a real record deal!

46:01.050 --> 46:01.920
I said I don't wanna
hear no more about it.

46:02.250 --> 46:03.150
<i>What the hell you know</i>
<i>about anything?</i>

46:03.420 --> 46:04.590
We've been in
this business

46:04.990 --> 46:06.360
- before you were wiping your own ass.
- Look it here.

46:06.760 --> 46:09.190
It's about damn time she started
taking advice from a nigger

46:09.500 --> 46:12.060
that don't wear no
stage makeup!

46:13.770 --> 46:15.300
Listen--

46:15.570 --> 46:16.930
Give me some more
of this!

46:17.240 --> 46:18.770
Give me some more
of all this stuff!

46:52.610 --> 46:53.800
It'll pass.

47:15.930 --> 47:16.790
...a couple of them
myself, too.

47:17.000 --> 47:18.460
Are you sure?

47:18.660 --> 47:21.400
(Chattering)

47:21.600 --> 47:23.730
(laughs)

47:23.970 --> 47:24.970
Jack: <i>Hey, Bessie.</i>

47:26.470 --> 47:28.240
This here Mr. Walker--
want to meet you.

47:29.780 --> 47:31.580
The hell you bring
him here for?

47:31.810 --> 47:33.040
<i>You remember him.</i>

47:33.350 --> 47:34.210
Brought him by a couple
of your shows.

47:34.580 --> 47:36.310
He wants to talk
to you about a record deal.

47:36.650 --> 47:38.280
- A real recording contract.
- Miss Smith,

47:38.650 --> 47:40.550
<i>I'd like to record</i>
<i>you for Columbia Records</i>

47:40.850 --> 47:42.290
<i>for our new</i>
<i>Race Records division.</i>

47:46.030 --> 47:48.430
What is a Race Record?
The one where they put a coon on the front?

47:48.660 --> 47:51.300
What? Um, no, ma'am.

47:51.660 --> 47:53.700
We at Columbia are taking
a different approach.

47:55.300 --> 47:57.430
I'm not interested
in your Race Records.

47:57.870 --> 48:01.710
And I'm not interested in wasting my
time singing no store-bought blues.

48:01.970 --> 48:03.140
<i>But we want your sound.</i>

48:03.440 --> 48:05.340
We want
the Bessie Smith sound.

48:05.640 --> 48:07.010
And it would be
your face on the ad,

48:07.450 --> 48:08.280
- nothing like those other records.
- I already sell out

48:08.550 --> 48:11.280
every show from
Philly to Chicago.

48:11.620 --> 48:13.280
Ain't nobody doing it
like I'm doing it.

48:13.620 --> 48:16.120
You'd attract
a broader audience.

48:16.460 --> 48:18.020
I've been doing
just fine without 'em.

48:18.320 --> 48:19.760
I can offer you
50 dollars a side.

48:19.990 --> 48:21.590
No royalties, of course.

48:21.790 --> 48:23.490
(Scoffs)

48:35.010 --> 48:37.170
Don't play with me now.

48:43.580 --> 48:45.220
J.G.

48:52.320 --> 48:54.990
Now, you want
what's in my jacket

48:55.190 --> 48:57.390
or in my pocket?

48:57.730 --> 49:00.930
(Scoffs) I already know what's in your pocket.

49:01.200 --> 49:02.800
Maybe you do,
maybe you don't.

49:03.040 --> 49:04.540
Now, what do you want?

49:04.740 --> 49:06.740
This or this?

49:07.010 --> 49:09.540
I want another velvet box.

49:16.720 --> 49:18.080
Marry me.

49:28.130 --> 49:29.790
You ou can't be
putting me upon no shelf.

49:30.100 --> 49:32.160
I ain't no
henpecked man, either.

49:36.100 --> 49:37.200
Take the chance on me.

49:51.820 --> 49:53.380
Come here, girl.

49:59.160 --> 50:00.660
Now, what's in
that other pocket?

50:00.860 --> 50:03.890
Oh. (Chuckles)

50:04.160 --> 50:08.500
Uh, just
a recording contract

50:08.730 --> 50:10.370
from Columbia Records.

50:10.570 --> 50:12.970
<i>125 a side.</i>

50:13.310 --> 50:15.040
That's double
what that man said.

50:15.370 --> 50:17.910
That's 'cause I'm fighting
for you now, baby.

50:19.510 --> 50:21.210
Well, maybe we should
tell Clarence.

50:21.510 --> 50:24.680
Uh-uh. This here is
me and you now.

50:34.260 --> 50:35.490
Man:
<i>All set. Let 'em know.</i>

50:35.890 --> 50:37.890
Man #2:
